article.headline: W. Carolina 117, Toccoa Falls 58
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. (AP) -- Antonio Russell scored a career-high 26 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead six players in double figures Monday as Western Carolina defeated Toccoa Falls, 117-58. Russell was 10 of 14 from the field, including two of three three-point attempts, for the 3-1 Catamounts. Jake Robinson had 17 points, Nick Aldridge had 14, Kyle Greathouse and Stan Johnson each had 12 and Brigham Waginger 11 for Western Carolina. Aldridge had four of the Catamounts 20 steals, a record set in the 2001-2002 season over Tennessee Wesleyan. Toccoa Falls, 4-5, was led by John Rychener with 14 points.
